			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The story behind this is:
<br />

<br />
There's a nifty spot in Seb some called the NG (necrosis/guardian) and others (namely me) call B2. It was a nice spot because there are 3 sepsis scarabs (and occasionally a higher level, slightly harder necrosis scarab) that almost always dropped a gem that sells for a good amount of plat like blue diamonds. It was such a good source of cash that one day someone had the bright idea to hijack the camp and to stay there 24/7. This happened on several servers. It was always a duo of a cleric and enchanter. On the Tribunal where I play they are called Lingxia and Legaato. They all seemed to speak English as a second language and usually took a long time to answer a tell. If, by chance, you happened to get the camp away from them, or did what a GM told me to do and inform them that they had to share, they would either start pulling frogs right into your fight spot or eventually pull a massive train on your head so you either evacced or died.
<br />

<br />
The reason they did this was to sell plat on auction sites. So, how did Sony handle this?  The perma-campers were clearly violating several rules that were upsetting players and hurting the economy of the game itself. Did those people get banned? Were they told to log the characters off for a certain amount of time every day? Did their Seb keys get disabled (a suggestion I gave to a GM)? Nope. They just nerfed the gem drops. This, for me, was really the straw that broke the camel's back. Instead of punsihing the perpatrators, they punished everyone in the game for the actions of a few. They did it not because it was the only way to protect the integrity of the game, something that I still would not have liked but could have understood, but because they were wusses who invoked mass punishment because it was the easiest way they could think of to handle the problem.
<br />

<br />
I've been seeing this stuff go on for four years now. this is most likely the end for me. as far as I'm concerned, Sony may as well have put into their patch message, "Please go play Warcraft."<br />_________________<br />Damonn Dayblaze
<br />
Mage of the Tribunal and All Around Awesome Dude.
<br />
No pretty pictures, no clever quote. Deal with it!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
